The course describes the main principles of motor control, age-related changes  in motor control and the effect of  physical training and inactivity to human motor functions. The main research methods of motor functions (neuromuscular electrical stimulation, dynamography, myotonometry, videography, goniography, etc.) and their application possibilities are described.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to improve the knowledge of students on motor functions in respect of gender maturation and aging, and physical activity.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: 1) understands the general principles of motor control and changes in motor function during lifespan; 2) knows the main research methods of kinesiology.
